riation and reinvention of modernista verse and the dynamics of her breakthrough poetics, a poetics that became a model for later women writers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aUruguayan poetryxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aUruguayan poetryxHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aUruguayan poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300183412.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles